  "prompt": "When and how did Gautama Buddha die?",
  "response": "Gautama Buddha, also known as Siddhartha Gautama, is believed to have died around 483 BCE (although some sources suggest a date around 400 BCE) in Kushinagar, a site in present-day India. His death is referred to as the Parinirvana, which is considered the final passing away and liberation from the cycle of birth and death (samsara).\n\nAccording to Buddhist tradition, the Buddha died at the age of 80. The circumstances of his death involve a brief illness. After delivering important teachings to his disciples, he lay down between two trees (often described as sal trees) and entered a meditative state. It is said that he encouraged his followers to continue practicing and seeking enlightenment. He then passed away peacefully, achieving Parinirvana.\n\nThe event is commemorated in many Buddhist cultures, and it is considered an important moment in the history of Buddhism, symbolizing the end of the Buddha's earthly existence and the attainment of ultimate freedom from suffering.",
